<item>
            <title>[LU-6907] Gerrit checkpatch (and derived scripts) is too noisy</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-6907</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Currently every time gerrit checkpatch reviewer makes a comment, it&apos;s sent to everybody subscribed to the ticket.&lt;br/&gt;
Add more bots like this and the email storm becomes quite big.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;But in fact gerrit REST API allows the script to have control over who gets the emails.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So I propose to change gerrit checkpatch reviewer to only send email to patch owner on error, and not send any emails to anybody on success.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Proposed patch is to follow shortly.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
